EnsDeconv

EnsDeconv (Ensemble Deconvolution) which uses ensemble learning to robustly estimate cellular fractions from bulk omics data.

How to cite EnsDeconv

Please cite the following publication:

Robust and accurate estimation of cellular fraction from tissue omics data via ensemble deconvolution
Cai, M., Yue, M., Chen, T., Liu, J., Forno, E., Lu, X., Billiar, T., Celedón, J., McKennan, C., Chen, W. and Wang, J.
 Bioinformatics. 2022 Jun 1 10.1093/bioinformatics/btac279

Installation

devtools::install_github("randel/EnsDeconv")
